NT||UP|44|cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|It was a sort of a mundane part score  hand but a couple of additional comments. All of you should bid 2D with my hand. If pard is on lead, you really want a diamond lead. Overcalls (especially 2 level) are not just for competing, but are often lead directing. So if you have a really nice suit, you should strain to overcall to make sure partner will lead it.|
PG| ***** 16 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Now, let's talk about TJ's pass. She has to decide what she thinks is likely to happen. Part of being a good bidder is trying to anticipate what a likely auction will be. So, if she thinks Kiri is likely to bid 2S and she is going to bid 3D over 2S, she should bid 3D right away. It is always better to make your bids as early as possible when you can. Makes it harder for the opponents to exchange info. However, with her hand it is not clear, nor is it clear if they have an 8 card fit.|
PG| ***** 17 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Other possible actions by Kiri are 3C and 2H (that is least likely). If over 3C, TJ was planning to bid 3D, then she should bid 3D right away. In other words, from TJ's perspective, the most likely bids by Kiri are 2S and 3C. If she is planning to bid 3D over those, then 3D right away is better. |
PG| ***** 18 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|One could make the argument that Kiri might pass, and we get to play 2D. That is true, but with our 8-card fit, unlikely. I am not saying that it is clear to bid 3D, but I am saying there are some good arguments for doing so right away.|
pg| ***** 19 ***** |


