^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Let's talk about 1NT over 1C (and 1D) which is one of my least favorite bids. It takes up a lot of room, and often wrong sides the contract. So, especially over 1C, you should strain not to bid 1N. In fact, sometimes if I am 3-3-3-4 (4 clubs, 3 in all other suits) I will bid 1D with 6 or 7 points just to avoid bidding 1NT. Then bid 2C as my 2nd bid if partner bids a major. Not saying you should do that, but on this hand 1D is clearly preferable to 1NT although we will end up in the same 1N :).|
