up|43|NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|We discussed the bidding and the way TJ played the contract was fine. However, you should get in the habit of counting out suits. Had TJ counted diamonds, she would have realized that only 1 diamond remained. So, she can safely play a spade before playing the @HA and make 2 or 3. But making your contract is never a bad idea.|
PG| ***** 36 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|1D over 1C leaves more bidding room for your side. Also 1N over 1C denies 4 diamonds. It is true on many hands bidding 1N rather than 1D will make no difference. But why not be more accurate when you can. The modern tendency is to bypass diamonds when you have a 4-card major. And if you want to play that simple way, that is fine. You could also play that you always bid 1D when you have 4 diamonds and a 4 card major. But almost no one does that any more. The simple rule is fine (always bid 4-card major rather than diamonds).|
PG| ***** 37 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|I use something a bit more complicated. I bid 1D if I am willing to take a second bid to show my 4-card major. So if I have a bad hand (6-9) I will bid my 4 card major rather than diamonds. But if I have a hand where I can take a 2nd bid, I will bid diamonds, particularly if my diamonds are 5+ or a nice 4-card suit. |
PG| ***** 38 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|If we did not play that 1D absolutely denies a 4-card major, then I clearly have to bid my major. If 1D denies a 4-card major, you could make a case for 2C, but that bypasses 1N which might be better.|
PG| ***** 39 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|If it goes 1C-1D-2C-2H, that is a game force (and partner is denying 4 card major). If it goes 1C-1D-1H, then 2H shows 9-10, 3H shows 11-12. If it goes 1C-1D-1N then 2H is rarely bid, that would also show a strong hand with 5+ diamonds and 4+ hearts. On this hand, we have an 8-card club fit, so 2C is fine. |
PG| ***** 40 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|One could argue, since my clubs are so good, even if TJ had a doubleton or singleton, 2C might be safer. So yes 2C over 1N would be quite reasonable. But if my club suit were not as good, say AQ98x, then 2C is less obvious.|
