^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Let's discuss my 3S bid. Cue bids of the opponent's suit can be confusing. The most common use is as a limit raise or better. Had I bid 2S right away that would be 10+ in support of clubs. The other use is as a stopper ask. If it looks like NT is a feasible contract, then a cue bid of the opponent's suit asks pard to bid 3N with a stopper. |
PG| ***** 81 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|That is what I meant in this auction. It is "asking" not telling. If I had a spade stopper I would bid 3N. Hence 3S must say I do not have a spade stopper. Some people call that a "Western cue" which is a very useful bid.|
